<p>The only point of contention I have is that there are cases where hardware develops an intermittent problem, it is failing but not reliably so. This rarely goes on for very long before &quot;It freezes/hard-resets occasionally&quot; becomes &quot;It won't turn on/finish booting period&quot;, but it does happen.</p>
<p>But yes. 98% likelihood goes to &quot;Sir, I understand that you are waiting for an important e-mail, but your internet service provider has nothing at all to do with whether or not there is electricity in your house.&quot;</p>

							</div>

								
					
