			<div class="content" id="post-content-1623355">
									

<p>I have never personally experienced an unrecreatable error. Under the same conditions, a machine will respond in the same way. The relevant conditions just often are not what one thinks they are.</p>
<p>Much like alien abduction, I'm prepared to admit that intermittent glitches may be real, but I would need more hard evidence. And, if either is indeed ever proven, we would have to re-write our current understanding of physics.</p>

